Package: langwidget
Version: 1.8.3
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10),
         python3-pyqt5,
         qtwayland5,
         libxkbcommon0
Recommends: fonts-dejavu-core
Maintainer: Whonix developers <whonix-devel@whonix.org>
Homepage: https://www.whonix.org
Description: Keyboard layout indicator for LXQt on Wayland (labwc)
 A lightweight keyboard layout indicator that displays the current
 keyboard layout as a short label (EN, DE, etc.) in the LXQt system
 tray. Designed for Wayland-only environments, specifically
 Whonix 18 with the labwc compositor.
 .
 Features:
  - Pure Python implementation (no compiled components)
  - Wayland-native (no XWayland required)
  - Uses StatusNotifierItem (SNI) via Qt for LXQt panel integration
  - Configurable layout-to-label mapping via JSON
  - XDG autostart and optional systemd user service
